 class, the first and second cases would be covered with a single test. I could add a test for both positive loadClass and fallback failure using an assertion for ClassNotFoundException. I’m curious if Class.forName in native might require metadata, and whether \\\"missing class\\\" names include active classes. Should I replace the int array test or add a third test?\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_F6FWjivTEhOLTznOi3LpDK5p|fc_0f60718b29e5bc3b0169f0d117615481919dfef1d8edf6d63e", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.netty/netty-all/4.0.23.Final/src/test/java/io_netty/netty_all/ClassLoaderClassResolverTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    @Test\n    void fallsBackToClassForNameForArrayDescriptors() throws ClassNotFoundException {\n        ClassResolver resolver = newResolver();\n\n        Class<?> resolvedClass = resolver.resolve(int[].class.getName());\n\n        Assertions.assertSame(int[].class, resolvedClass);\n    }\n\n    private static ClassResolver newResolver() {\n        return ClassResolvers.cacheDisabled(ClassLoaderClassResolverTest.class.getClassLoader());\n    }\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void fallsBackToClassForNameForArrayDescriptors() throws ClassNotFoundException {\n        ClassResolver resolver = ClassResolvers.cacheDisabled(new ArrayDescriptorFallbackClassLoader());\n\n        Class<?> resolvedClass = resolver.resolve(int[].class.getName());\n\n        Assertions.assertSame(int[].class, resolvedClass);\n    }\n\n    private static ClassResolver newResolver() {\n        return ClassResolvers.cacheDisabled(ClassLoaderClassResolverTest.class.getClassLoader());\n    }\n\n    private static final class ArrayDescriptorFallbackClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private ArrayDescriptorFallbackClassLoader() {\n            super(ClassLoaderClassResolverTest.class.getClassLoader());\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Class<?> loadClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (int[].class.getName().equals(name)) {\n                throw new ClassNotFoundException(name);\n            }\n            return super.loadClass(name);\n        }\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 292, "output": 2520, "cacheRead": 22528, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25340, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777389815116, "responseId": "resp_0f60718b29e5bc3b0169f0d0f78d1881919dbe75f1cd1a3a0b"}}
